⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Genetic Drift
node POP · POP · ⟦Genetic Drift:POP:bcd92c⟧

WHO   — Genetic Drift — chance · founder & bottleneck
WHAT  — Evolution by luck, not fitness: in a small population, which alleles pass on is partly a coin-flip.
WHERE — POP · Population Dynamics  Framework inputs: ecology, epidemiology, population genetics; Asimov's Foundation; verified & cited  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Life Science)
WHY   — Because selection isn't the only force — chance moves the gene pool too, and small numbers amplify it.
HOW   — By sampling error across generations: alleles can fix or vanish for no reason but luck.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Selection has a reason; I don't. In a small enough population I can erase a good gene or fix a useless one, by chance alone.

